<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-01-31T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-01-31T10:00:00-05:00" n="205" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d205">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">851.5151/1701: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-01-31T10:00:00-05:00">January 31, 1938—10
                                        a.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>52. For Cochran from Secretary of the Treasury.<note n="10" xml:id="d205fn10">Marginal note: “Telephoned by Mr. Lochhead,
                                    Treasury Department.”</note> Your 160. The reference to the
                                Tripartite Agreement and France which the French Financial Attaché
                                to the United States reported to Rueff was given only as background
                                information to the press and not as a direct statement or interview.
                                In the circumstances Secretary Morgenthau does not wish his name to
                                be used in connection with it.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>